Authen-OATH-OCRA

This is an implementation of the OATH Challenge Response Algorithm
as defined by OATH (http://www.openautentication.org).

Please note that some of the code was influenced by the 
Authen::OATH module. 
I am indebted to Kurt Kinkaid 
who wrote the Authen::OATH module.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Authen::OATH::OCRA

You can also look for information at:

    OCRA: OATH Challenge-Response Algorithm RFC
        http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6287

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Authen-OATH-OCRA

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Authen-OATH-OCRA

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Authen-OATH-OCRA

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Authen-OATH-OCRA/


